message.content: cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.SY - This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it proposes a congestion avoidance scheme for ATM networks. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category as it deals with rate indication and capacity estimation. Additionally, it may be relevant to the Communication and Networking (cs.COMM) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories as it involves network switches and virtual channels. Finally, it may be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category as it aims to achieve efficiency, fairness, and controlled queueing delays.
